<subSubSection id="769253EE874CB84675144BF5BC942E5B" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="2206A084B40E4147D96199671A7DBE04" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EB0A13157EC68F1E14B209E7B8AEF277" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
Species characterised by dark lines between contiguous conspecific thalli, pale usually endolithic thallus, perithecia leaving shallow to deep pits in the rock, very variable involucrellum, ascospores (18-)23-28(-32) 
<normalizedToken id="840BE01F09F8471BF4086D47315CB68C" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(8-)11-13(-15) mm, morphologically rather similar to the Finnish species of the 
<taxonomicName id="5E99F759C5DB7021527B3F5D851E523C" genus="V." lsidName="V. subtilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="subtilis">
<emphasis id="3CB2B994228368DD8C6FBA8276E3F49C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. subtilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex, but the sequence divergence in ITS 4.5-6.8%.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
