<subSubSection id="FF7D30BAAFCC7621249E14CFE0777FFD" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="notes">
<paragraph id="46219A8611359EA20D8875F49F7F9B99" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0138406DC986101EFDA585B78B0074BC" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
Based on ITS sequences, 
<taxonomicName id="B5862FDCC81E584D7503C9EBBF25372D" genus="V." lsidName="V. vacillans" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="vacillans">
<emphasis id="B848FC4B8D07E20F795F4BA4018DE1E7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. vacillans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is genetically well distinct from other 
<taxonomicName id="44935EBB9F3AF12CCD688B64C1003F8B" class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Verrucariaceae" genus="Verrucaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Verrucaria" order="Verrucariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6A83EFE5357ACD380BD8CB9DCF71F3A8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Verrucaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species. However, it may be confused with several other species. 
<taxonomicName id="93930BE2B87F7F1649F63CD3917E26A4" authorityName="Pykaelae &amp; Myllys" authorityYear="2020" class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Verrucariaceae" genus="Verrucaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Verrucaria vacillans" order="Verrucariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="vacillans">
<emphasis id="4E65F8481FF92D65246C0F5EED0E10D7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Verrucaria vacillans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most difficult to separate from 
<taxonomicName id="F071859C14BF3840708EEDC203B04C39" genus="V." lsidName="V. cavernarum" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="cavernarum">
<emphasis id="98745B49D1BE48E29EC9AD024437DB4F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. cavernarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="001BC67765785315AF080E25629D83B4" genus="V." lsidName="V. difficilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="difficilis">
<emphasis id="965A4BDC6C4E76FC33B5E5D659AC19FD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. difficilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="CC609943749C08366B4508FFBDB58C6E" genus="V." lsidName="V. subtilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="subtilis">
<emphasis id="AF9F074F0A4DDC01F277BC5439A072CE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. subtilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In these three species, dark lines between contiguous conspecific thalli are never present. 
<taxonomicName id="83B354AF05F2F7FF669DABA592852CE4" authorityName="Pykaelae &amp; Myllys" authorityYear="2020" class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Verrucariaceae" genus="Verrucaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Verrucaria cavernarum" order="Verrucariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="cavernarum">
<emphasis id="2F676979951474255075354E71BE6C18" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Verrucaria cavernarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="640182AD5B3BF90543C899C730F92ED3" genus="V." lsidName="V. subtilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="subtilis">
<emphasis id="2EFBF8E2AE94B4BBEAE1BCB57727A76E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. subtilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have an involucrellum seldom exceeding half of the exciple (and then only in a minority of perithecia). The exciple of 
<taxonomicName id="767D84DC7152AB88EDD38E7D689D7051" genus="V." lsidName="V. subtilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="subtilis">
<emphasis id="31654FF0343852730970B76935719180" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. subtilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is sometimes pale (although usually dark). The spores tend to be slightly broader in 
<taxonomicName id="9C78B5F7765051F66014EA4CFEE389E6" genus="V." lsidName="V. vacillans" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="vacillans">
<emphasis id="EFFB630EDAC9AC8A6207C1FD46B106F0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. vacillans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than in 
<taxonomicName id="6D2C883AF8AC6E5F4F1A0E366E5E89A9" genus="V." lsidName="V. subtilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="subtilis">
<emphasis id="D7F523D7634C5D109D731C8454756E32" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. subtilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="649720CC4F5CA4F0329E03BF6F0A4357" genus="V." lsidName="V. vacillans" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="vacillans">
<emphasis id="B8FE0141E8E86E1A1D17C35A21CCC660" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. vacillans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without dark lines and with a short involucrellum may not be possible to separate from 
<taxonomicName id="E343F02EBAFA636F3077F1F9C78BB56D" genus="V." lsidName="V. cavernarum" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="cavernarum">
<emphasis id="24C2C4C6C7C3B3FD819CB4F1BE432B17" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. cavernarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="7F22C7A0BFE6CDB4688CDF8FE7710345" genus="V." lsidName="V. subtilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="subtilis">
<emphasis id="FF884C8E9CECCC8C72A9E49561EA4D52" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. subtilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by morphology. Specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="2556EB8D39646F2321C441CDCA78842D" genus="V." lsidName="V. vacillans" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="vacillans">
<emphasis id="C1BCA298DF33434D27905A3B72566141" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. vacillans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with a deep reaching involucrellum may not be separable from 
<taxonomicName id="8D0BA2F4A5C2312457FAD8ACA4CA6783" genus="V." lsidName="V. difficilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="difficilis">
<emphasis id="EA88F0E891145AB83103FF4A30A40125" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. difficilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
if dark lines are absent. 
<taxonomicName id="7B47C3D32B7A16A12AEE57DAD8456DCC" authorityName="Pykaelae &amp; Myllys" authorityYear="2020" class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Verrucariaceae" genus="Verrucaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Verrucaria vacillans" order="Verrucariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="vacillans">
<emphasis id="235FD2AC8B93FA6B03C398639075852A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Verrucaria vacillans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may also be confused with 
<taxonomicName id="57B8BC92D74F3C7CAE385CC5B2B736D3" genus="V." lsidName="V. devergens" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="devergens">
<emphasis id="94948269E221426AC4566C2FB7F85040" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. devergens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="928B9A6993769F0D9A3831A67523A4BE" genus="V." lsidName="V. kuusamoensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="kuusamoensis">
<emphasis id="EAEB6524DF7D4354D3B61723A8E991F7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. kuusamoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="5B3B8CD157B424985E0ADD882405D42A" genus="V." lsidName="V. epilithea" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="epilithea">
<emphasis id="8E2A728C1B965BA39D020C50928EFD54" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. epilithea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="286565E4127E6CCA12770155A08F2947" genus="V." lsidName="V. muralis" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="muralis">
<emphasis id="88ACFA252A6EB9DF2434432A4CC2F4B3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. muralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="909897D2CB22E530CDE801E18AF1F1EE" authorityName="Pykaelae, Kantelinen &amp; Myllys" authorityYear="2020" class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Verrucariaceae" genus="Verrucaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Verrucaria kuusamoensis" order="Verrucariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="kuusamoensis">
<emphasis id="9FF1457163F983DBD5D092527BF0AA9B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Verrucaria kuusamoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has an involucrellum usually exceeding half of the exciple, larger spores and dark lines are rather rare. 
<taxonomicName id="F42A2F437CE2A2B5D956FEEE6D961CBE" authorityName="Nyl., Flora 55: 362" authorityYear="1872" class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Verrucariaceae" genus="Verrucaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Verrucaria devergens" order="Verrucariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="devergens">
<emphasis id="1E339718450422F317963760DE17B797" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Verrucaria devergens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has larger spores and the involucrellum is usually absent or sometimes apical. 
<taxonomicName id="78054AC42B188019463E173DB1688535" class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Verrucariaceae" genus="Verrucaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Verrucaria epilithea" order="Verrucariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="epilithea">
<emphasis id="CCF70718E912353E1A360BAE40D0A517" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Verrucaria epilithea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D17E8F31AE5A016B65937994DB1154C9" genus="V." lsidName="V. muralis" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="muralis">
<emphasis id="A09EBBE91D40A3D06C00E623A047ED41" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. muralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have perithecia not leaving pits or the pits are shallow, the spores do not exceed 26 mm in length and dark lines are absent.
</paragraph>
